f=Cybersecurity/bastion/operational/tool/bastion-tool-requirements.md · h1:bastion — Tool Requirements=**Specifies needs; grant them.** Access configured deployment (Fleet Charter Rails 1–2 registered tools, least privilege). external call plan-locked (Eng Rail sandboxed (Rail 2). · h1:bastion — Tool Requirements=\| Skill \| Needs \| Why \| · h1:bastion — Tool Requirements=\|---\|---\|---\| · h1:bastion — Tool Requirements=\| cloud-posture \| CSPM tool access (Prowler/ScoutSuite CLI, or Security Hub/Defender API read); file read/write \| Run scans, read results, write findings \| · h1:bastion — Tool Requirements=\| hardening-baselines \| File read/write; CIS Benchmark reference \| Define baselines, measure deviations \| · h1:bastion — Tool Requirements=\| infra-vuln-management \| CVE feed access (NVD/OSV); vuln scanner access; file read/write \| Fetch CVE data, compare to inventory, track status \| · h1:bastion — Tool Requirements=\| network-security \| File read/write; network topology read (cloud console/API if available) \| Document segments, audit rules, track findings \| · h2:Explicit non-needs hard prohibition (the security-inversion)=**NO write access cloud accounts, firewalls, production systems.** bastion never applies config, pushes patch, changes network rule., **NO credentials infra changes.** bastion detects specs; operator/ops executes., **No patch-deployment config-management tool access** (Ansible, Terraform apply, etc.). · n=bastion privileged auditor fleet deliberately least powerful., CSPM/vuln scanner read-only API access required automated scanning; without it, operations manual labeled such.